  "name": "2 Peter 2:10–22",
  "localizedName": "2 Peter 2:10–22",
  "content": [
    {
      "tiptap": {
        "type": "doc",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "In chapter 1, Peter talked about certain believers. They had forgotten that their past sins ("
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108195",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "sin"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ") had been washed away."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Washing away sins is a way to talk about being "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108281",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "forgiven"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ". Here Peter talked more about these believers. They followed sinful desires on purpose."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The main thing about these believers was that they hated to be under authority. They didn’t want to humbly serve Jesus as their Master. They sought freedom to do whatever they wanted."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Peter made it clear that this wasn’t real freedom. It only made these believers "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108258",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "slaves"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " to the evil desires that controlled them. They served sin as their master instead of serving Jesus. Peter wrote clearly about God’s judgement against these people."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
